<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Azumi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I play alot of MMORPGs so maybe a few of these suggestions only apply to them, but ill try anyway.<BR>1. Shortkeys for your magic and health potions , ctrl + 1 or something like that , so you dont get distracted whilst in combat. <BR>2. (already suggested ) a stand ground key , ie when this key is held down , no matter where you left click it will stay on the spot.<BR>3. Re-spawns , i just dont like going back to the menu to load a saved game.Maybe the guy you first meet's house is the respawn point. If no respawn then maybe autosaves and when you die you instantly go back to the last save.  <BR>4. There should be more of a perminant weapons and armor shop ( maybe there is ) because i dont know if that guy you trade with for weapons is supposed to lock his door but he did with me and now i cant find anywhere to buy weapons. <BR>5. Monster and Your health should be above your head so that you can watch it more carefully.<BR>6. Get rid of the silly words when you pull a lever ... i mean i walked around pulling levers and they ALL open doors, so after the first time i would say its fairly obvious what it has done and he should no longer ask what.  <BR>7. Restrict certain areas to certain lvls , a lvl requirement probably would have stopped me finishing the demo at lvl 1. <BR>8. NPC's should NOT attack you for a simple mistake.  I picked up a carrot in the weapons trader place and he asked if i was interested in it , i said no and he killed me. ... Instead of doing that why dont you remove the item from inventory when i say no.  <P>These suggestions are probably to my personal liking.  I understand many people have many personal preferences that others may or may not like. <BR>lemme know what you think <BR>-azumi  </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Soulflyer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hey Azumi, welcome to the forum !!<P>To give some answers to your questions: <P>1) Just open the potions pop up and click a key from F1 to F4 (I guess, could be more ..) and the key will be assigned.<BR>3) I don't think a respawn in an ordinaire RPG would be logical, it would make the game too easy and you could always try a situation over and over again instead of forcing you to use your brains.<BR>4) You can buy and sell goods at almost all NPC's in the village .. just press the trade icon on the left side of the conversation box.<BR>6) I don't mind them that much  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"> ...<BR>7) I think this isn't that logical. Have you finished the demo at level 1 ??? Are you sure, have you met the dragon rider and where you trown back to the main menu while getting a message, this isthe end of the demo ??? if you did  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/icons/icon14.gif"> !!!<BR>8) Yo should just be more careful in the  <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/div.gif"> world, some things are really realistic and stealing is not a nice thing !!!  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif">  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Founder and first member of the <B>Guild of New People Welcomers and other druidic occupations</B><P><I>Seduce my mind and you can have my body, find my soul and I'm yours forever.</I><BR>Today might be a good day to visit <A HREF="http://feelgreat.at/divine-divinity" TARGET=_blank>My divinity fanpage.</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Crythe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT